## Test Compliance Analysis

Analyzing spec-to-test alignment for `library-add`:

### Coverage Summary

| Requirement | Scenarios | Covered |
|-------------|-----------|---------|
| Import resource to library | 3 | 2 (platform canonicalization partially via unit tests) |
| Auto-detect resource type | 4 | 4 (unit tests + E2E) |
| Auto-detect resource name | 3 | 2 (missing name edge case difficult to trigger - filename always produces name) |
| Auto-detect description | 2 | 2 |
| Handle existing resources | 2 | 2 |
| Support dry-run mode | 1 | 1 |
| Validate canonical document | 2 | 1 (invalid rejection via unit test) |
| Validate library after update | 2 | 1 (corruption hard to simulate) |
| Discover library path | 3 | 2 (env and flag covered) |
| Canonicalize platform documents | 4 | 2 (DetectPlatform and IsCanonicalFormat covered) |

### Notable Gaps

1. **Platform canonicalization E2E** - Not end-to-end tested with real OpenCode/Claude Code files (unit tests cover detection)
2. **Invalid document rejection** - Unit tests cover but not E2E
3. **Library corruption** - Difficult to simulate; atomic writes mitigate
4. **Default library path discovery** - Not tested (would use real home directory)

**Assessment**: Coverage is adequate for the feature. Core happy paths and error cases are tested. The E2E tests pass successfully.

